article.headline: Ohio 71, Brown 62
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio (AP) -- Jeff Halbert hit four of his five 3-pointers and scored 14 points to lead Ohio to a 71-62 victory over Brown on Saturday. After falling behind 12-5 at the outset, Ohio (2-4) responded with an 18-4 run over a 5{-minute stretch to take a 23-16 lead. The Bobcats never trailed again. Ohio had four players in double figures, including Thomas Stephens and Jaivon Harris with 11 points each. Harris, who did not start after a poor shooting performance in a loss last week to Toledo, hit three of his four shots from the field in the second half. Junior college transfer Clay McGowen also had 11 points off the bench and helped Ohio to a 37-32 rebounding advantage with 10 rebounds. Jamie Kilbourn led Brown (2-5) with 14 points and 13 rebounds. A Halbert 3-pointer with 10:13 left in the game gave Ohio a 58-48 lead. The Bears cut the lead to two points at the 6:36 mark on a layup by Jason Forte, but in their next nine possessions they turned the ball over three times, missed five shots from the field and a free throw. Halbert's 3-pointer with 54 seconds left gave Ohio its biggest lead at 69-58.
